These are just notes for myself for how to debug and check the correctness

rm maindebug 

compile with:
mpicc -o maindebug -Iinclude src/stencil_template_parallel.c -g

or with:
mpicc -o maindebug -O2 -fopenmp  -Iinclude src/stencil_template_parallel.c -g

then execute with:
mpiexec -np 2 gnome-terminal --wait -- gdb -x ./gdb_commands ./maindebug

Another thing to theck the code is animate the heat expansion with:
python plot_parallel.py data_parallel -x 128 -y 256 --sx 1 --sy 2 -n 100 --save parallel.mp4

but make sure that you've compiled the code with the dump decommented